<h1>Webstore Options</h1>
<h2>Option 1: Stripe</h2>
<h3>Summary</h3>
<p>Stripe is an online payment processing software that offers the ability for websites to implement e-commerce. This payment processing service is reputable with business such as Amazon, Zoom, Lyft and  <a href="https://stripe.com/customers">many others.</a> This option also has the ability to set up a <a href="https://stripe.com/use-cases/marketplaces">marketplace</a> on a website where they offer everything you need to onboard service providers, manage payments and send payouts out.</p>
<small>Stripe also offers very detailed and extensive developer <a href="https://stripe.com/docs">documentation</a> that can allow for fast and easy implementation.</small>

<h3>Pricing</h3>
<p>As for pricing, Stripe let's their customers have access a complete payments platform with pay-as-you-go pricing. They state that their are no hidden fees, monthly fees or setup fees to use their service. Instead, Stripe charges 2.9% + 0.30 for each successful transaction. They also offer a <i>'customized option'</i> if there is a need to design a custom package for your business. Here is a <a href="https://stripe.com/pricing">link</a> to view the pricing information.</p>

